items.name: FlowEtl
items.description: This is a framework designed for the creation of testable components which can be interconnected via arbitrary inputs and outputs and those components can be executed in the correct order (inputs satisfied before running) automatically. This is useful since it aids developers in thinking in the paradigm where they plan components ahead of time, allowing for simpler reuse and refactoring later. At yahoo! this was created for a ETL like framework & pipeline, but its applications are not  limited to solely that, since the concept itself is generic.

items.name: Txt2PDFConverter
items.description: The project of 'txt' to 'pdf' file converter, written in Java, using the iText library (http://itextpdf.com/). The code contains two programs, IN- working only in its current directory & OUT- working everywhere. It allows a user to convert a 'txt' file to a 'pdf' file. It has some useful functions which I found missing in free software, e.g. auto fitting of text without requiring from user to guess appropriate font size.
